description: Try our easy to follow Baked Salmon Frittata recipe. Absolutely delicious with the best ingredients from Woolworths.
name: Baked Salmon Frittata Recipe | Woolworths

recipeInstructions.text: Wash small potatoes and prick several times. Place on a microwave safe plate in the microwave. Cook on high for 3-4 minutes or until just tender. Set aside to cool. Slice. Preheat grill on medium heat.
Whisk eggs and cream in a bowl. Roughly chop salmon. Crumble feta. Stir salmon and feta into egg mixture.

Heat olive oil in a 22cm non-stick frying pan over a medium heat. Add potato and cook for 5 minutes. Add zucchini to potato and stir until combined. Pour egg mixture over vegetables. Stir until combined.

Reduce heat to low and cook for 10-12 minutes or until egg sets around edges. Put pan under preheated grill and cook for 5 minutes or until eggs are set and frittata is golden. Stand for 5 minutes. Serve with rocket.
